.TH Num.isinf 3 2025-11-29 "Tomo man-pages"
.SH NAME
Num.isinf \- check for infinite number
.SH LIBRARY
Tomo Standard Library
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.BI Num.isinf\ :\ func(n:\ Num\ ->\ Bool)
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Checks if a number is infinite.


.SH ARGUMENTS

.TS
allbox;
lb lb lbx
l l l.
Name	Type	Description
n	Num	The number to be checked. 
.TE
.SH RETURN
`yes` if `n` is infinite, `no` otherwise.

.SH EXAMPLES
.EX
assert Num.INF.isinf() == yes
assert (1.0).isinf() == no
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR Tomo-Num (3)
